.\" Manpage for cmedit.
.TH CMEDIT 1 "2026-07-01" "cmedit 0.1.1" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
cmedit \- a from-scratch terminal text editor
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B cmedit
.RI [ FILE .\|.\|.]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B cmedit
is a modeless terminal text editor written from first principles in Haskell.
It is a cross between Microsoft's Edit (msedit) and GNU nano: a drop-down menu
bar, real mouse support, system-clipboard integration and nano-style on-screen
shortcut hints. No TUI framework is used \(em raw-mode terminal control, the
input parser, the diff renderer and the menus are built directly on VT/ANSI
escape sequences and the POSIX termios API.
.PP
If one or more
.I FILE
arguments are given they are opened on startup; otherwise an empty buffer is
created.
.SH KEY BINDINGS
.TP
.B ^S
Save the current file.
.TP
.B ^O
Open a file.
.TP
.B ^F
Find.
.TP
.B ^G
Go to line.
.TP
.B ^Z
Undo.
.TP
.B ^X
Cut.
.TP
.B ^V
Paste.
.TP
.B ^Q
Quit.
.TP
.B F10
Open the menu bar (also Alt+letter).
.SH FILES
.TP
.I FILE
One or more text files to open. Files with a
.I .csv
or
.I .tsv
extension can be opened in a spreadsheet-style table view.
